pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.3-2) stable; urgency=medium

  * fix: eliminate duplicate scheduled snapshots. A new disk's FlexVol was
    created carrying the configured snapshot_policy while the same policy was
    also set on the VM's consistency group, so both fired and the disk was
    snapshotted twice (until a best-effort reconcile cleared the volume, and
    permanently in any path where it did not). Member volumes are now created
    with policy 'none' — the consistency group is the sole owner of the
    scheduled-snapshot policy — and the snapshot reserve is sized from whether
    a schedule is configured. Verified live on PVE 9.1 / ONTAP 9.17.1.

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Tue, 16 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200

pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat: cluster-wide per-VM locking (pmxcfs, keyed SVM+VMID) around all
    consistency-group mutations — snapshot create/rollback/delete, membership
    changes, CG cleanup, cross-VM disk moves, policy reconcile — closing the
    cross-node races (lost backup snapshots, duplicate same-named snapshots,
    disks stranded outside their CG).
  * feat: snapshot integrity guards. CG snapshots are only taken/restored
    through actual CG members (per-volume fallback with a loud warning
    otherwise); a CG rollback is refused when the snapshot is partial or does
    not cover all current member volumes (a disk added after the snapshot);
    deleting a PVE snapshot removes all same-named ONTAP snapshots (CG and
    per-volume); SVM-scoped async (202) results are verified by polling, and
    snapshot creation fails loudly when unconfirmed.
  * feat: VM starts and migrations survive a management-API outage — path()
    consults a local namespace->device cache (UUID-matched against live
    sysfs) before any REST call; the NVMe portal list is cached per daemon
    lifetime so activation costs no REST round-trip.
  * feat: capacity awareness — allocations that obviously cannot fit are
    refused upfront; status() warns when a FlexVol passes 90% of its autosize
    ceiling, before ONTAP takes the namespace offline.
  * feat: hourly stranded-object sweep in activate_storage — warns about
    namespace-less FlexVols left by interrupted allocations and base volumes
    missing their pve_base snapshot; reaps empty consistency groups
    (snapshots included) under the per-VM lock.
  * feat: NVMe/TCP-TLS pre-flight at activation (tlshd running + PSK present
    in the kernel keyring, else fail fast); the connection check matches
    controller addresses against this storage's portals instead of
    short-circuiting on any controller; check_connection probes the REST
    endpoint over HTTPS; status() runs under a 10s timeout.
  * changed: deleted disks go through the ONTAP volume recovery queue by
    default (admin-recoverable for the retention period); the new
    force_delete option restores immediate deletion. Note: a parked FlexClone
    pins its base image until purged/expired.
  * changed: path() fails loudly — an ONTAP-offline namespace is named, a
    not-yet-visible device is awaited with backoff then fails with a clear
    fabric error — instead of returning the /dev/ontap-nvme-pending
    placeholder. New SVM-scoped storages require svm_capacity at add time.
  * fix: cross-node CG create race converges on the winner's CG; pvesm
    remove refuses to delete secrets while volumes still exist on ONTAP;
    stale CGs left by a reused VMID are purged before adoption; connect/TLS
    failures get actionable certificate diagnostics; changing NVMe auth
    secrets warns about the host-NQN re-registration window.
  * feat: scheduled snapshots are now atomic across a VM's disks. The
    snapshot_policy is applied to the VM's ONTAP consistency group instead of to
    each FlexVol, so policy-driven snapshots are crash-consistent across all of
    the VM's disks (ONTAP fences I/O across the CG). Member FlexVols are kept at
    snapshot_policy 'none' to avoid duplicate per-volume schedules. On ONTAP
    < 9.12.1 a disk that cannot join the CG falls back to a per-volume schedule;
    base templates carry no schedule.
  * feat: changing snapshot_policy (pvesm set --snapshot_policy) reconciles all
    of the storage's existing consistency groups and volumes immediately from
    the update hook, instead of waiting for the next disk operation. Bounded and
    best-effort (a config update never fails if ONTAP is briefly unreachable).

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Tue, 09 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200

